6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 733, L.D. 1114, “An Act to Provide That
10 Spouses and Children of Corrections Officers Who Die in the Line of Duty Receive a
11 Pension”
12 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the enacting clause the following:
13 'Mandate preamble. This measure requires one or more local units of government
14 to expand or modify activities so as to necessitate additional expenditures from local
15 revenues but does not provide funding for at least 90% of those expenditures. Pursuant to
16 the Constitution of Maine, Article IX, Section 21, 2/3 of all of the members elected to each
17 House have determined it necessary to enact this measure.'
18 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1511 in the indented paragraph in the 6th line (page 1,
19 line 9 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "age." the following: 'The county
20 commissioners of each county shall pay a pension required by this section from county
21 funds.'
22 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
23 number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment adds a mandate preamble to the bill and further clarifies that county
2266 commissioners of each county must pay these pensions from county funds.
2277 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
